node.text:
Do you remember all those little diecast West Coast Choppers bikes I used to sell at Wal*Mart?? 
Well my partner in that business, “Fred”. Is my partner in our Ammo business : Ammo Inc. 
Exciting times for this venture!
Not only did we just purchase Gunbroker.com. We also own Jagemann Brass in Manitowoc Wisconsin. That’s right down the road from out New Ammo Inc Facilities. I don’t usually toot my horn much on business stuff, but this one is pretty Damn cool! 

If you dig this stuff please follow these...
@ammoincusa 
@jessejamesammo 
@gunbroker 

Also if you’re interested in stock.
We are “POWW” on Nasdaq👍🏽

Thank you!🙏🏻🙏🏻

#jessejames

node.text:
The margin for error building our JJFU Damascus 1911’s is zero. 

If they were carbon steel or stainless. There are several ways and processes to address a blemish or a flaw or incorrect dimension.

Not with Damascus. You can’t weld it. All surface work, machine work, broaching, gun smithing and final finishing has to be perfect. Any flaws will be on full display.

If things go wrong and it’s not perfect??

Back into the forge and I smash them and use the material to forge weld into new Damascus stacks. Most likely used for our @jesse_james_culinary Damascus chef knives.

Out of all the Damascus pistols I’ve made. I’ve had 3 that were not passable. 
It’s pretty disheartening after spending a solid year on something. Then having to smash it. But like I always say. Never justify the time spent. If it sucks it sucks.

#jessejames

@popeofwelding 

www.JJFU.com
